icity on a time-scale of a thousand orbital periods. It\nmay thus be a promising mechanism for intermittently regaining balance with the\nexponential growth of eccentricity from the eccentric Lindblad resonances and\nmay also help explain the occurrence of \"bursty\" dynamics such as the superhump\nphenomenon.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 9 Apr 2018 21:43:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-05-02"}
